                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "5cxy1",
                          "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Software architecture is the foundation upon which all code is built. Without a clear architectural vision, projects inevitably devolve into tangled dependency graphs that resist change and breed bugs.\n\nClean Architecture, as popularized by Robert C. Martin, offers a disciplined approach to organizing code that keeps business logic at the center while pushing infrastructure concerns to the edges.\n\n## The Dependency Rule\n\nThe fundamental rule of Clean Architecture is simple: source code dependencies must point inward.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.7,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
